  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "For injuries received on account\nof negligence of Great Northern\nemployees, John T. Carver, driver\nof transfer wagon, this morning\nbrought suit for $4,000 in the SUI\nperior court, alleging that he has\nreceived permanent internal in\njuries. He alleges that on Jan. 20,\nwhile he was unloading a car of\nfurniture, G.. A. Rosebrook, yard\nforeman. ordered string of cars\nswitched onto the track where the\nfurniture car was located. The\nstring struck the furniture car just\nas Carver had grasped hold of a\nheavy piece of furniture. The\nshohck of the cars coming together\nthrew him over bale of wire upon\nhis back."
    }
